runs.description: somehow went from meh– to yeah!
real rainy one up the sligachan valley/ very lovely in the rain. beautiful mist and rolling hillages.
run around the hills at the back of sconser. found a new high path with great ol views across the bay
big hills and down into the back of the quarry!
run along the footpath from sligachan to peinchorran - totally beautiful, running so lightfooted and surefooted and fastfooted and the air was warm but there was a soft mist hanging in the air
same as yesterday. not as beautiful.
refreshener before wee maggie's birthday party
refreshener day after hangover. hard- not enough food.
rainy day, sun cleared up so i went out. loop up round forestry and hydro. quite lovely in the end.

oof been a while! been so rainy and party at the weekend. waited for a break in the rain, ended up being 6pm, beautiful light, but the chill of autumn has truly set in, ran along the road from through cleadale to the forestry, nice brisk pace to get the warmth flowing through me, then round the back and down past the hydro. beautiful light so ran up to the road from george and sarah’s, then along a bit and down to the catholic church and along the coast.
road, hydro, then through the coast hills past laig
up round the cliff along cleadale- eagles? in the mist
along the road, fast pace, then to the orchard, ate 4 apples, and ran back, fast pace. beautiful day. bright and colorful.
simple run up the road– to the forestry and back
ease back in, terrible form, mellified ankles and a cauterised lung
lap of brockwell, lap of ruskin
HALF - lapping it up at brockwell (5x) before getting nearly home and realising i totally had enough energy to bust half a slice of marathon pie
bacchus and illness have slowed and weakened me - 10k
"you're doing good, keep it up" - 3x brockwell 10k
going jogging- no! it's a run- okay, it's a jog
stomach cramps; the much needed gas relief only came 100yds from the front door
la virutas de oro de los árboles
back up and running! with god in my ankle!
a journey into my own soul
set sail on the good ship st. legs
careful on those trotters, johnny. don't put them out of action just once they're got rolling.
the sun is out, the hills are rolling, and the cowshit puddles are splashing up my calves.
sun running amongst storm doris's smithereen banquet
pain in my glute, still having a hoot
R.I.P. left shoe, cherished protector of left foot, beloved brother of right shoe.
just may be the most beautiful run of my life. fresh hills of sprouting green under a clean and cloudless azure sky!
why run on an injury instead of letting it heal? because the sun and earth command it!
kisses on m' knee, knives on m' sole
badger wears a pulsing maggot coat
sometimes it's nice just to walk
like a treadmill in an oven- why am i turning myself into a rotisserie chicken?
su u  u   u  u un
found a dog, returned a dog
flush out the weekend bad things
at least a 3-course taster menu of flies on my palate
coffee setting hot laps on the racetrack of my veins
☄ o baby! air back in my lungs - no longer powered by snot
'05 paula radcliffe knows—and i now i know—why it's better to run in the countryside than on city streets
tops off in the rain; or: child-"haha! why's he naked?" mother-"he's not naked, he's got shorts!"
butterflies dancing in my headstream turbulence
maggots in the blackberries really harsh my vibe
got a bit swampy out here
everyone's out walking today– horses and women, dogs and men
word to the wise: don't go for a long run with a scotch bonnet still lurking in your bowels
the kind of day bono loves to harp on about
my body is a whorehouse playing host to a revolving cast of injuries
it sure is orange out there
ankle gave a terrifying 'POP' 2 miles in, but i managed to squeeze in another 6 before the swelling set in
robbed of the return leg by the notorious bandit 'el garmino batterizo'
back out in the open field shod in nought but fancy plimsoles
really pounding the numbers into these shoes
runners knee done fucked up my runners freedom
my runner's knee cant hold back my runner's glee
harshwind tryna strip my bones naked
t a r m a c
work the billows of the lung & feed the flames
warm wakes the joy of singing birds
water me– i am a plant
oh this is how it feels
forgot what dry earth felt like
please spring, bud forth your merry face
"I was talking to my maker! You weren't supposed to hear..."
hard to keep a steady pace with cornish beauty in your face
coastal cowboy with the land's end lasso
let the mind run, & jog the memory. runs like this make me think, maybe i really could run forever
peach juice chin and sea salt skin
nothing like the feel of sea on your bare danglers
day of rest for a day of zest
hard to keep a steady pace with all these blackberries begging to be eaten
got a "Poldark!" heckle for running topless along the cornish cliffs
very eerie are dairy farms in the evening fog
ruins of mines & green valley streams
seems like the whole world's got the grump today. 'cept that one girl, smiling for everyone.
summer's never over when you're RICH!
wheat heads look up to drink
crow with a cracker in it's mouth
good to slop around in some mud again
barely a run, barely a walk
blood red silhouettes the hilltop windmills
rain so light and lovely it's scarcely rain at all
worrying amount of pain for the first time in a while. like, enough-to-turn-back pain.
chased by tame dogs, exalted by an indian infant
chinese child dancing in the sun
lookin' at me with that cow eye
shed a tear for the woodland
W E T  &  S L O P P Y
stray sunlight thru the fallen pines (16.6)
makin' friends on the mountain top
maybe i'll come up here every day– hang out with the crows
a nice run can become an even nicer walk
the sun is a drug, and gosh is it potent 🌞

a run to rag out the last of the weekend depressivations- 
cold and crisp evening run in the dark. 
so long since i'd run in glasgow at night- 
the moon was strong.

in linn park
the sun's low light cut through the mist of the waterfall
creating an impossible beauty- 
the water was shining- 
everything and me were aloft in the same moment
rainy eve run around - tracing back the memories in the tower blocks and fog draped hills
sunday sun, smile fishing around glasgow

the windy after-gusts of storm malik.
words of encouragement from a shop painter,
dressed all in white with grey hair - 
"keep going boy, you got a good rhythm going"
boy? how nice to hear! 
there's still boy blood flowing in these bones. 
the eyes of youth— or the legs of youth. 
i'll hold onto 'em. 
i'll hold 'em dear.

sun was out, insects were born and flying, 
took in the view from an alleyway on giffnock hill 
that had the whole of the city laid out beneath me,
white towers and brown brick and green trees,
all bright with chlorophyll — and the white peaks in the distance,
glittering against the clear blue sky behind them,
and the clouds above, holding it all in, keeping it alive for us,
— benevolent gardeners.

fishing for trees, riding the hills,
fighting the wind, finding friends (will & maria) atop the lookout of the city.

runnin on a couple 'a drumsticks 🍗
i feel the rhythm as much as i hear it

runnin' down the back alleys
i find the rat alleys of my mind

as i glide through flower gardens –
i know my sleeping spirit hardens
runnin' on a couple 'a hard-boiled legs

sun is hot for the season –
shining on boys playing cricket in the car park – 
they had the right idea – 
it's a long way back to beers in the garden

did i run? or did i dream it?
am i running on dreams?

the sky was away from the earth,
where the ground was green and verdant,
	screaming with brightness,
tufts of grass waving out to me in the wind –
the sky swamped with light and cloud,
swirls of dark light peeling itself backward
	away from everything.
my body felt light as the earth,
but sympathetic to the heavy, pervasive energy of the sky.

drops of rain imbue the air
with a sense of continuity –
like my skin never ends
it begins as the trees do –
with the shining green of spring.

I wish my gaze as Pure as the Birds'
Alighting on a rusted cow pen
                    as if it were a Tree.
